{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17648622","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17648622"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:55:40+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:55:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18322"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18322","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18322"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.7,0.05,0.05,0.05,0.15]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11040"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107843"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11040","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11040"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18322"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90265"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8412"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25616"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25617"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25845"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40124"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107843","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107843"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ESarcomas can be found in many different types of body tissues.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is a type of soft tissue sarcoma?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Leiomyosarcoma","Osteosarcoma","Chondrosarcoma","Ewing\u0027s sarcoma","Wilms tumour"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELeiomyosarcoma\u003C/strong\u003E is a type of soft tissue sarcoma that arises from smooth muscle cells. It can occur in any location where smooth muscle is present, including the uterus, gastrointestinal tract, and extremities. Here is an example, where the tumour is occupying most of the stomach (Image).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOsteosarcoma\u003C/strong\u003E is a type of bone sarcoma, not a soft tissue sarcoma. It typically arises in the metaphysis of long bones, such as the femur or tibia, and is most common in adolescents and young adults.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChondrosarcoma\u003C/strong\u003E is another type of bone sarcoma that originates from cartilage cells. It is more common in adults and typically affects the pelvis, femur, and shoulder girdle.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEwing\u0027s sarcoma\u003C/strong\u003E is a highly aggressive bone tumour that can also affect soft tissues, but it is primarily classified as a bone sarcoma. It is most common in children and young adults.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWilms tumour\u003C/strong\u003E is not a soft tissue sarcoma but rather a type of kidney cancer (nephroblastoma) that primarily affects children. It arises from embryonic kidney cells and is the most common type of renal tumour in children.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Soft tissue sarcomas originate from mesenchymal tissues such as muscle, fat, and connective tissue.","Leiomyosarcoma is a type of soft tissue sarcoma that arises from smooth muscle cells.","Bone sarcomas, such as osteosarcoma and chondrosarcoma, are distinct from soft tissue sarcomas."],"references":["Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2021). Textbook of Orthopaedics, 2e-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Mohan, H. (2018). Textbook of pathology. Jaypee Brothers Medical Publishers","Momodu II, Savaliya V. Osteomyelitis. [Updated 2023 May 